                    right-hand man and CTO Jack Holloway (both from Triple-I). Hardware architecture was based on work
                    by researchers at the M.I.T. Artificial Intelligence Laboratory and the Lisp Machine project in 1974
                    (thanks to the close proximity of the Symbolics Cambridge Research Center).

